page.title: 10MORE BIRDS IN DOLPHINTON
page.content: Birds of Prey - Common Buzzard Sparrowhawk Kestrel. All nest here, Occasional Goshawk. Magpie Jackdaw Rook Hooded/Carrion Crow. Owls - Tawny Short-eared Long-eared. Game Birds - have deceased in past decade. Red Grouse Black Game and Partridge nests scarce. Hand reared Pheasants released in woods and coverts to supplement wild stock. Wood Pigeon Collared Dove and Stock Dove Cuckoo Great Spotted Woodpecker Starling Swift Swallow House Martin Sand Martin. Finches - Gold Green Bull Chaffinch Linnet. Warblers - Willow Wood Garden Chiffchaff Goldrecrest Firecrest Treecreeper Dipper. Wagtails - White Pied Water Robin Wren. Tits - Great Coal Blue Marsh Long-Tailed Fly catcher Song Thrush Mistle Thrush Blackbird Fieldfare Redwing Wheatear Skylark Woodlark Meadow Pipit Whinchat
